ackModal_main_2528414\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hxf1665702924646.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hxf1665702924646.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hxf1665702924646.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hxf1665702924646\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Load Balancing Over Time\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A system can be overloaded during certain periods and be almost idle during other periods. If this is the case, there are opportunities for more efficient use of the system.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hxf1665702924646__p_d46592e1_d46593e1_d46594e1\">You can:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hxf1665702924646__li_d23195e1_d23196e1_d23197e1\">Suspend jobs with low priority to times with low system activity\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hxf1665702924646__li_d23198e1_d23199e1_d23200e1\">Combine jobs with low priority into a single batch job and submitting this job as a low-priority background process\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hxf1665702924646__p_d46595e1_d46596e1_d46597e1\">The data for system load over time, such as the number of concurrent users and the access stress rates, are collected during inception and analyzed using techniques such as access path analysis. The following illustration shows a possible result:</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"hxf1665702924646__fig_d46598e1_d46599e1_d46600e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Sample Load Balance Data</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Sample load balance data\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/sampleloadbalancedata.jpg?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hxf1665702924646__p_d46604e1_d46605e1_d46606e1\">The Uniface Router can balance loads over time. During peak times, there can be a pool of Application Servers handling incoming client requests. As requests come in, the Uniface Router gives each request to an available, matching server that has handled most requests. After the peak, as client requests become fewer, many servers become idle. You can ensure that the Uniface Router stops these idle servers by setting the <code class=\"ph codeph\">/maxidle</code> setting in the UST (server type) definition.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/geh1665702717743.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/maxidle</a><p>Specify the maximum time a shared Uniface Server (identified by its server name (UST)), is allowed to be idle (not handling any requests).</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528414\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528414\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Load Balancing Over Time Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Load Balancing Over Time A system can be overloaded during certain periods and be almost idle during other periods. If this is the case, there are opportunities for more efficient use of the system. You can: Suspend jobs with low priority to times with low system activity Combine jobs with low priority into a single batch job and submitting this job as a low-priority background process The data for system load over time, such as the number of concurrent users and the access stress rates, are collected during inception and analyzed using techniques such as access path analysis. The following illustration shows a possible result: Figure 1. Sample Load Balance Data The Uniface Router can balance loads over time. During peak times, there can be a pool of Application Servers handling incoming client requests. As requests come in, the Uniface Router gives each request to an available, matching server that has handled most requests. After the peak, as client requests become fewer, many servers become idle. You can ensure that the Uniface Router stops these idle servers by setting the /maxidle setting in the UST (server type) definition. Related Links /maxidle Specify the maximum time a shared Uniface Server (identified by its server name (UST)), is allowed to be idle (not handling any requests). Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}